<doc id="41585" wikidata="Q7247168" url="?curid=41585" title="Proceed-to-select">
<text>In telecommunications, proceed-to-select is a signal or event in the call-access phase of a data call, which signal or event confirms the reception of a call-request signal and advises the calling data terminal equipment to proceed with the transmission of the selection signals. 

Examples of proceed-to-select pertain to a dial tone in a telephone system.

