<doc id="41610" wikidata="Q16911585" url="?curid=41610" title="Push-to-type operation">
<text>Push-to-type operation: In telegraph or data transmission systems, that method of communication in which the operator at a station must keep a switch operated in order to send messages. 

Push-to-type operation is used in radio systems where the same frequency is employed for transmission and reception. 

Push-to-type operation is a derivative form of transmission and may be used in simplex, half-duplex, or duplex operation. &quot;Synonym&quot; press-to-type operation.

This is similar to Push-to-talk operation for radio phone communications.

